# Testes CrewAI para Rules

## Mock de Agent

```python
import pytest
from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch
from crewai import Agent, Task, Crew

@pytest.fixture
def mock_agent():
    agent = MagicMock(spec=Agent)
    agent.role = "Pesquisador"
    agent.goal = "Pesquisar sobre {topic}"
    agent.backstory = "Pesquisador experiente."
    agent.tools = []
    return agent

def test_agent_tem_role_definido(mock_agent):
    assert mock_agent.role == "Pesquisador"
```

## Testando Task Execution

```python
@pytest.fixture
def mock_task(mock_agent):
    return Task(
        description="Pesquisar sobre IA",
        expected_output="Relatorio com fontes",
        agent=mock_agent,
    )

def test_task_tem_expected_output(mock_task):
    assert "Relatorio" in mock_task.expected_output
    assert mock_task.agent is not None
```

## Testando Crew

```python
@patch("crewai.Crew.kickoff")
def test_crew_executa_sequencialmente(mock_kickoff, mock_agent):
    mock_kickoff.return_value = "Resultado da pesquisa sobre IA Generativa"

    research_task = Task(
        description="Pesquisar sobre {topic}",
        expected_output="Relatorio",
        agent=mock_agent,
    )

    crew = Crew(
        agents=[mock_agent],
        tasks=[research_task],
        verbose=False,
    )

    result = crew.kickoff(inputs={"topic": "IA Generativa"})
    assert "IA Generativa" in result
    mock_kickoff.assert_called_once()
```

## Testando Tools do Agent

```python
def test_agent_possui_tools_necessarias():
    agent = Agent(
        role="Pesquisador",
        goal="Pesquisar",
        backstory="Experiente",
        tools=[search_tool, scrape_tool],
    )
    tool_names = [t.name for t in agent.tools]
    assert "search" in tool_names
    assert "scrape" in tool_names
```

## Testando Context entre Tasks

```python
def test_task_context_encadeamento():
    task1 = Task(description="Pesquisar", expected_output="Dados", agent=mock_agent)
    task2 = Task(
        description="Escrever",
        expected_output="Artigo",
        agent=mock_agent,
        context=[task1],
    )
    assert task1 in task2.context
```

## Convencoes

- `MagicMock(spec=Agent)` para mocks com interface validada
- `@patch("crewai.Crew.kickoff")` para evitar execucao real
- Fixtures para agents e tasks reutilizaveis
- Testar configuracao (roles, tools, context) separado de execucao
- Testes de integracao com `@pytest.mark.integration`
- `verbose=False` em testes para output limpo
