# CrewAI Rule Testing

## Mock Agent

```python
import pytest
from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch
from crewai import Agent, Task, Crew

@pytest.fixture
def mock_agent():
    agent = MagicMock(spec=Agent)
    agent.role = "Researcher"
    agent.goal = "Research about {topic}"
    agent.backstory = "Experienced researcher."
    agent.tools = []
    return agent

def test_agent_has_defined_role(mock_agent):
    assert mock_agent.role == "Researcher"
```

## Testing Task Execution

```python
@pytest.fixture
def mock_task(mock_agent):
    return Task(
        description="Research about AI",
        expected_output="Report with sources",
        agent=mock_agent,
    )

def test_task_has_expected_output(mock_task):
    assert "Report" in mock_task.expected_output
    assert mock_task.agent is not None
```

## Testing Crew

```python
@patch("crewai.Crew.kickoff")
def test_crew_executes_sequentially(mock_kickoff, mock_agent):
    mock_kickoff.return_value = "Research result about Generative AI"

    research_task = Task(
        description="Research about {topic}",
        expected_output="Report",
        agent=mock_agent,
    )

    crew = Crew(
        agents=[mock_agent],
        tasks=[research_task],
        verbose=False,
    )

    result = crew.kickoff(inputs={"topic": "Generative AI"})
    assert "Generative AI" in result
    mock_kickoff.assert_called_once()
```

## Testing Agent Tools

```python
def test_agent_has_required_tools():
    agent = Agent(
        role="Researcher",
        goal="Research",
        backstory="Experienced",
        tools=[search_tool, scrape_tool],
    )
    tool_names = [t.name for t in agent.tools]
    assert "search" in tool_names
    assert "scrape" in tool_names
```

## Testing Context Between Tasks

```python
def test_task_context_chaining():
    task1 = Task(description="Research", expected_output="Data", agent=mock_agent)
    task2 = Task(
        description="Write",
        expected_output="Article",
        agent=mock_agent,
        context=[task1],
    )
    assert task1 in task2.context
```

## Conventions

- `MagicMock(spec=Agent)` for interface-validated mocks
- `@patch("crewai.Crew.kickoff")` to avoid real execution
- Fixtures for reusable agents and tasks
- Test configuration (roles, tools, context) separately from execution
- Integration tests with `@pytest.mark.integration`
- `verbose=False` in tests for clean output
